Title: Divergences in formal variational calculus and boundary terms in
  Hamiltonian formalism
Author: Vladimir O. Soloviev
Comments: 15 pages, TeX macro included, no figures, talk given at "Symposium on
  Differential Geometry and Mathematical Physics", Warsaw, May 1995
\\
  It is shown how to extend the formal variational calculus in order to
incorporate integrals of divergences into it. Such a generalization permits to
study nontrivial boundary problems in field theory on the base of canonical
formalism.
